item.title: How do i get jdk?
item.dc:creator: @ZA_H ZÃ©H
item.description:
@ZA_H wrote:

[quote=“Bubbsy7, post:3, topic:257800”]If it’s for your compiler use this,
right click on your compiler then edit

@echo off title Owner Rawr64 Compiler echo Now Compiling "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_07\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java echo Finished Compiling pause <------------------------------------------------------Copy and Paste that[/quote]

yes use that if your compiling if not go to http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
and download the latest version of JDK it will say something like JDK version 6 update 11.

then the place the

C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_07\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java

with your update which will be 11
so it should look like this

C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_11\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java
